\emph on
Product measure.

\emph default
 The product measure of two 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

-finite measure spaces 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}=\left(X_{1},\mathcal{A}_{1},\mu_{1}\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{2}=(X_{2},\mathcal{A}_{2},\mu_{2})$
\end_inset

 is the measure space 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}\times S_{2}=(X,\mathcal{A},\mu)$
\end_inset

, where
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $X=X_{1}\times X_{2}$
\end_inset

;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}=\sigma(X,\mathcal{A}')$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}'=\{s_{1}\times s_{2}\mid s_{1}\in\mathcal{A}_{1},s_{2}\in\mathcal{A}_{2}\}$
\end_inset

;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

 is the unique measure satisfying 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(s_{1}\times s_{2})=\mu_{1}(s_{1})\mu_{2}(s_{2})$
\end_inset

.
