\begin_layout Definition

\emph on
Point measure.

\emph default
 Given a nonempty set 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and some 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in X$
\end_inset

, we define the point measure on 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 at 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 to be 
\begin_inset Formula $\mbox{point}(x,X)=(X,\mathcal{A},\mu)$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{A}=\{\emptyset,X,\{x\},X\setminus\{x\}\}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(\{x\})=1$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mu(X\setminus\{x\})=0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

