\begin_layout Definition

\emph on
Measurable function.

\emph default
 Given two measurable spaces 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}=(X_{1},\mathcal{A}_{1})$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{2}=(X_{2},\mathcal{A}_{2})$
\end_inset

, the triple 
\begin_inset Formula $(S_{1}.S_{2},f)$
\end_inset

 is called a measurable function if 
\begin_inset Formula $f:X_{1}\rightarrow X_{2}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{-1}(s)\in\mathcal{A}_{1}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $s\in\mathcal{A}_{2}$
\end_inset

.
