Measurable function.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $(X_{i},\mathcal{A}_{i})$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1,2$
\end_inset

, be measurable spaces.
 A function 
\begin_inset Formula $f:X_{1}\rightarrow X_{2}$
\end_inset

 is measurable with respect to 
\begin_inset Formula $(\mathcal{A}_{1},\mathcal{A}_{2})$
\end_inset

 iff 
\begin_inset Formula $f^{-1}(s)\in\mathcal{A}_{1}$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $s\in\mathcal{A}_{2}$
